title: Yoga for Overthinking Kids | Yoga for Children | Calm Your Busy Mind | KPop Demon Hunters
description:
Welcome to Yoga for Overthinking for Kids — a gentle, calming routine for busy minds.

If your thoughts feel like a shaken glitter jar, this class helps everything settle down through slow breathing, grounding poses, and a cozy final rest.

In this video, we practice:

belly breathing to feel safe and steady
soothing stretches for the neck, back, and hips
grounding standing poses for focus
relaxing twists and a peaceful final rest
Perfect for: after school, before bed, stressy days, big feelings, or anytime your mind won’t slow down.

Reminder: Yoga should never hurt. Move gently, take breaks, and make it comfortable.

Comment below: What helps your mind feel calm—breathing, stretching, or resting?

#KidsYoga #MindfulKids #Overthinking #AnxietyRelief #CalmMind #BedtimeYoga #YogaForKids #Relaxation #BreathingExercises

title: 14 Min Mobility Flow Yoga Workout (No Equipment) | Day 14 New Year Workout Snack Series
description:
🎁 Grab your free full-length Barlates workout + a bonus 5-min booty burner when you reply “yes”!  
👉 https://subscribepage.io/Barlates

Description
This Day 14 mobility flow workout is a feel-good, dynamic stretch session designed to improve mobility, posture and overall movement. The workout is performed with 50 seconds of work and 10 seconds of rest, and no equipment is needed.

You’ll move through a yoga-inspired flow with some standing work and mostly mat-based exercises. Expect plenty of hip-opening movements including pigeon variations and low side lunge hip stretches, along with posture-focused exercises to release tension in the shoulders and upper back. A great session for recovery, flexibility and leaving you feeling open and refreshed.

The New Year Workout Snack Series is a 4-week program with 5 short workouts per week, created to help you rebuild consistency after the festive season. The workouts are short, sharp and highly effective — ideal for busy schedules. Do one or two when time is tight, or stack multiple workouts together for a longer session. The series includes a wide variety of styles so there’s something for everyone.

description:

End your day with this gentle bedtime wind-down yoga sequence, designed to help you release stress, relax your body, and prepare for deep, restful sleep. #BedtimeYoga #YogaForSleep #WindDownYoga #NightYoga #RelaxingYoga

This calming practice includes slow shoulder releases, neck movements, seated twists, hip openers, windshield wipers, and soothing stretches that can be done on the floor, on a mat, or even on your bed. No equipment is required, making it perfect for nights when you feel tired, stiff, or mentally overwhelmed.

The session finishes with deep belly breathing and relaxation, helping your nervous system shift into rest mode.

02:36 Neck Rolls & Gentle Neck Release
04:21 Arm Hugs & Upper Back Stretch

✨ Perfect for:
• Better sleep and relaxation
• Releasing neck, shoulder, hip, and lower-back tension
• Stress relief after a long day
• Bed yoga and no-mat yoga routines
• Beginners and all levels

Practice this sequence regularly to unwind, slow down, and drift into peaceful sleep.
